===Etymology 2===

====Glyph origin====
One of the 324 simplified characters introduced by the {{w|Republic of China}} ({{w|Kuomintang}} government) in 1935 as a simplified form of {{l|zh|Ťó•}} but was later retracted in 1936.<!-- Refer https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:ROC24_SC2.jpg --> Prior to that <big>ŤĎĮ</big> and {{l|zh|Ťó•}} were two homonyms that were not related with one another. <!-- Note: ŤĎĮ is not found as a variant form of Ťó• in any historical dictionaries. -->

In the 1956 {{w|Chinese Character Simplification Scheme}} by the People's Republic of China, <big>ŤĎĮ</big> was once again listed as a simplified form of {{l|zh|Ťó•}}<!-- Refer https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/śľĘŚ≠óÁį°ŚĆĖśĖĻś°ą --> which was succeeded by {{l|zh|ŤćĮ}} based on the radical simplification of {{l|zh|Á≥Ļ}} to {{l|zh|Áļü}}.<!-- Refer https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/Áį°ŚĆĖŚ≠óÁłĹŤ°® (1964) or Section 3 of śľĘŚ≠óÁį°ŚĆĖśĖĻś°ą (1956) -->

